AWS ke steps

S3 BUCKET
Create bucket
Name yo bucket

1. Head over to your AWS account 
2. Click on S3 Bucket 
3. Click on Create bucket 
4. Give it a name & without changing any settings click on create bucket 

5. Go to properties and enable the static website option. This will unlock more options to you
(Yeh option end main hai - scroll down) 

6. Give it a name index.html


7. Click on Save Changes, this will provide you with a link
(Scroll neechu neechu tak for this also)


8. Go to permissions and ublock all public access (upar hi hai, don’t scroll down - use your eyes)


9. In permissions itself go to bucket policy and edit it to: (agar no policy display Hua toh Matlab empty hai)
PASTE THIS CODE ON THE LEFT SIDE DUMBASS & change the bucket name also 
// Code 

{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Sid": "PublicReadGetObject",
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Principal": "*",
            "Action": [
                "s3:GetObject"
            ],
            "Resource": [
                "arn:aws:s3:::Bucket-Name/*"
            ]
        }
    ]
}

// Code


10th step onwards:
Go to VSCODE
Open a file in a folder
Close the welcome page
(don't open file)


Press control & oui oui (~) button to OPEN TERMINAL
Type  npx create-react-app client 
(This creates a react app for ya)

Now, you type 
  cd client
  npm start  (this starts your website)
( copy paste from par these 2 commands)

Now chrome opens - react website ho gaya

CONTROL C PRESS KAR

type: npm run build
( this creates a build folder on the left side dekhna inside client folder)

Go back to AWS now
Click on ‘Objects’
Then click on Upload 
Then click on Add Files (INSIDE BUILD ONLY)
Upload all files (only files)
Add Folder
Click on static and upload the entire folder

Then go to properties, scroll ekdum neechu neechu and click on the click and TAADDAAA














